    "username": "godofprompt",
    "nickname": "God of Prompt",
    "text": "A business can look healthy and be quietly running out of cash.\n\nThese 7 prompts turn AI into a finance analyst.\n\nPricing, unit economics, runway, projections, and scenario models.",
    "quoted_tweet": null,
    "url": "https://twitter.com/godofprompt/status/2066419185161478415",
    "time": "2026-06-15 15:15",
    "created_at": "Mon Jun 15 07:15:00 +0000 2026",
    "id_str": "2066419185161478415",
    "is_retweet": false
  },
  {
    "username": "godofprompt",
    "nickname": "God of Prompt",
    "text": "1. The Price Setter\n\nI'm pricing [product or service] for [target customer].\n\nWalk me through 3 pricing approaches: cost-plus, value-based, and competitor-anchored. Show the number each one points to.\n\nTell me which fits my situation and why.\n\nThen name the price I'm probably",
    "quoted_tweet": null,
    "url": "https://twitter.com/godofprompt/status/2066419197232791618",
    "time": "2026-06-15 15:15",
    "created_at": "Mon Jun 15 07:15:03 +0000 2026",
    "id_str": "2066419197232791618",
    "is_retweet": false
  },
  {
    "username": "godofprompt",
    "nickname": "God of Prompt",
    "text": "2. The Unit Economics Breakdown\n\nHere's my price: [price], and roughly what it costs me to deliver one: [costs].\n\nBreak down the unit economics. What I make per sale after costs, the margin, and what's quietly eating it.\n\nInclude the costs I'm likely forgetting: payment fees,",
    "quoted_tweet": null,
    "url": "https://twitter.com/godofprompt/status/2066419208884486151",
    "time": "2026-06-15 15:15",
    "created_at": "Mon Jun 15 07:15:06 +0000 2026",
    "id_str": "2066419208884486151",
    "is_retweet": false
  },
  {
    "username": "godofprompt",
    "nickname": "God of Prompt",
    "text": "3. The Runway Calculator\n\nHere's my cash on hand: [amount]. Monthly money in: [revenue]. Monthly money out: [expenses].\n\nCalculate my runway in months and the date the cash runs low.\n\nShow how that date moves if revenue drops 20% or costs rise 20%.\n\nTell me the latest month I'd",
    "quoted_tweet": null,
    "url": "https://twitter.com/godofprompt/status/2066419220636975254",
    "time": "2026-06-15 15:15",
    "created_at": "Mon Jun 15 07:15:09 +0000 2026",
    "id_str": "2066419220636975254",
    "is_retweet": false
  },
  {
    "username": "godofprompt",
    "nickname": "God of Prompt",
    "text": "4. The Projection Builder\n\nBuild me a simple 12-month financial projection for [business].\n\nStart from these assumptions: [revenue drivers, growth rate, main costs].\n\nShow revenue, costs, and cash by month, and state every assumption out loud.\n\nFlag the one assumption the whole",
    "quoted_tweet": null,
    "url": "https://twitter.com/godofprompt/status/2066419232242614755",
    "time": "2026-06-15 15:15",
    "created_at": "Mon Jun 15 07:15:11 +0000 2026",
    "id_str": "2066419232242614755",
    "is_retweet": false
  },
  {
    "username": "godofprompt",
    "nickname": "God of Prompt",
    "text": "5. The Scenario Modeler\n\nTake my projection and run three scenarios: best case, base case, worst case.\n\nFor each, change the 2 or 3 assumptions that matter most and show how the ending cash position shifts.\n\nTell me which scenario I should actually plan around.\n\nName the early",
    "quoted_tweet": null,
    "url": "https://twitter.com/godofprompt/status/2066419243907006960",
    "time": "2026-06-15 15:15",
    "created_at": "Mon Jun 15 07:15:14 +0000 2026",
    "id_str": "2066419243907006960",
    "is_retweet": false
  },
  {
    "username": "godofprompt",
    "nickname": "God of Prompt",
    "text": "6. The Break-Even Finder\n\nHere's my pricing and costs: [fixed costs, cost per unit, price].\n\nTell me how many units or customers I need to break even, and by when at my current pace.\n\nShow how that number changes if I raise the price 10% or cut a fixed cost.\n\nPoint to the single",
    "quoted_tweet": null,
    "url": "https://twitter.com/godofprompt/status/2066419255479046236",
    "time": "2026-06-15 15:15",
    "created_at": "Mon Jun 15 07:15:17 +0000 2026",
    "id_str": "2066419255479046236",
    "is_retweet": false
  },
  {
    "username": "godofprompt",
    "nickname": "God of Prompt",
    "text": "7. The Numbers-to-Decision Brief\n\nHere's my model and the numbers: [paste].\n\nTurn it into a one-page brief for a decision: the call I'm facing, what the numbers say, the recommendation, and the risk.\n\nLead with the recommendation, not the spreadsheet.\n\nIf the numbers don't",
    "quoted_tweet": null,
    "url": "https://twitter.com/godofprompt/status/2066419267109859582",
    "time": "2026-06-15 15:15",
    "created_at": "Mon Jun 15 07:15:20 +0000 2026",
    "id_str": "2066419267109859582",
    "is_retweet": false
  },
  {
    "username": "godofprompt",
    "nickname": "God of Prompt",
    "text": "Run them in order and you go from a price to a defensible financial plan: the price, the margins, the runway, the projection, the scenarios, the break-even, the call.\n\nThe prompts run the math, but you own the assumptions and the decision they lead to.",
    "quoted_tweet": null,
    "url": "https://twitter.com/godofprompt/status/2066419278690296161",
    "time": "2026-06-15 15:15",
    "created_at": "Mon Jun 15 07:15:22 +0000 2026",
    "id_str": "2066419278690296161",
    "is_retweet": false
  },
